dc_description_s: New Jersey Deparment of Conservation and Development. Division of Geology and Topography. Atlas Sheet 37 (1936) New Jersey Geological Survey. Relief shown by 10 and 5 ft. contour intervals and spot heights. Depths are shown by soundings in feet at mean or half tide. Title was not given. Region covered: Cape May County. Original survey 1884; principal features revised 1913, 1928, 1935. Original survey amd revisions to 1913 made under direction of C. C. Vemeule, Topographer. Revision of 1935 by L. L. Plummer, Topographic Engineer. Inland waterway route from N. J. Dept. of Commerce and Navigation. The shore lines of tidal waters, and the triangulation are mainly from the U.S. Coast and Geodetic Survey.
dc_publisher_s: Trenton, N.J. : New Jersey Geological Survey, 1936.
